  <prompt>
    Build hierarchical memory composition that orchestrates the three primitives from
    tasks 064 (compression), 065 (pinned context), 066 (selective recall) into a single
    `IMemoryCompositionService` consumed by the chat prompt builder. Layers per spec
    FR-44:
    - **Recent verbatim**: last 10 turns as-is
    - **Compressed mid-distance**: turns 10-50 as summary blocks (from task 064)
    - **Retrieved old**: turns 50+ via similarity recall (from task 066)
    - **Pinned context**: pinType-grouped items (from task 065) — always included
    Respects 8K total budget (NFR-10) — when over budget, drops in priority order:
    retrieved old → compressed mid → recent verbatim oldest first; pinned NEVER dropped.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior AI platform engineer with familiarity with token budget orchestration +
    memory layering patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Composition service produces a single memory block consumed by chat prompt assembly;
    correct layering; budget enforcement; pinned items always present.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
